1. Storage drivers on the Image and Container:
# docker build command to create a image
# docker run command to run a container with a image

Two layers in the docker storage:
Image Layer:

Image layer: Source code in this layer is read only
Container layer: Read and writer access

If a developer changes the code then it will impact on Images and bacause the same image is used in the other deployment.
It will automatically copy the source code from image layer to container layer. For testing purpose we can do changes in the container layer.

But if container destroys then all the data from the container will be destroyed.

